 abstract = {A syndicate is defined to be a group of individuals who must make a common decision under uncertainty that will result in a payoff to be shared jointly among them. In this paper, the normative criterion of Pareto optimality is employed to determine the construction, and conditions for existence, of a group utility function and a consensus of the members' probability assessments.},
